{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Calibri;}{\f1 Courier New;}}\paperw11907\paperh16840\margl1440\margr1440\margt1080\margb1080\fs22 Daily Expense Tracker\line \line Assignment Information\line Dar es Salaam Institute of Technology\line Civil Engineering Department\line Module: Programming Fundamentals for Technicians (GST 05117)\line Class: OD24CE-2 | Assignment Type: Group | Assignment No: 3\line Group Number: 11 | Submission Date: March 1, 2026\line \line Group Members\line 1. ABDULAZIZ MAHYORO (240121429579)\line 2. LAWRENCE MMATAMBWE (220121417491)\line 3. ELIAH HANGO (240121476067)\line 4. HUSSEIN OMARY (240121449049)\line 5. ROBERT JAMES (240121479897)\line 6. GIDEON OLANG'U (240121429421)\line 7. MOSES MFUSE (24012317533)\line 8. GLORIA DAUDI (240121453512)\line \line Brief Explanation (One-Page Summary)\line In this mini project, our group focused on a clear problem that can be solved using basic C concepts learned in class. The objective of this work is to take user input, apply program logic step by step, and produce understandable results.\line In this project (Daily Expense Tracker), menu-driven expense tracker for recording category, note, amount, and summary statistics.\line \line How the Program Works\line 1. It shows a clear prompt/menu to the user.\line 2. It accepts and validates user input to avoid wrong values.\line 3. It processes data using conditions, loops, and calculations.\line 4. It prints final results in a readable format.\line \line Concepts Practiced\line - Arrays and structs\line - Input/Output\line - Loops and conditionals\line - Functions\line - Numeric aggregation\line \line Sample Output (short example)\line === Daily Expense Tracker ===\line 1. Add Expense\line 2. View All Expenses\line 3. Summary\line 4. Exit\line Choose an option: 1\line Enter category (Food/Transport/Utilities/Other): Food\line Enter note: Lunch\line \line Presentation Note\line This mini project is intentionally simple, focused, and easy to explain during presentation.}